column5: Between all the hospital and clinic visits, and poor weather, there has been little time for fishing. I finally got out for a day with the son for some local perchin. Nor a lot of fish, but no dinks in the mix.     Also been puppy sitting my sons little newcomer.  He's a short little rascal. 1/2 Jack and 1/2 Daschund. Only 10 weeks and gets along famously with Casey.
Nice puppy! Good to hear ya got out on the ice.. I havent been out yet.. Was hoping to hit Erie next weekend, but the weather doesnt look so good for that now.....
Hi Captain  Sounds like you have been one busy fella!!  Good you got out Looks like a Fun day.  You will hafta get some measuarable Perch after Feb 1  Rick
Looks like things are getting better for you. Glad to hear and happy Perchin.   Art
Great to see you got out Capt'n,but,let's hope,the fish coming after Feb 1 are just a bit bigger. lol.
WTG Bruce. Good to see you got into some..
Nice one Bruce....supper must hvae been good
Good show Big Ug!  Gotta embrace that winter weather while ya can... it goes by too quick and become a little less every year it seems.
